<emphasis id="B956EAE90507FF8DFBE0F88C98AC4405" box="[1135,1269,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="47">E. dandara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D780507FF8DFA89F88C99364405" authorityName="Soares &amp; Soares" authorityYear="1946" box="[1286,1391,1848,1874]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="11" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis id="B956EAE90507FF8DFA89F88C99364405" box="[1286,1391,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="47">E. fulvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D780507FF8DFF32F8EA9D10442F" box="[189,329,1886,1912]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="11" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="B956EAE90507FF8DFF32F8EA9D10442F" box="[189,329,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="47">E. mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D780507FF8DFE08F8EA9E65442F" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1839" box="[391,572,1886,1912]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="11" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyacanthus">
<emphasis id="B956EAE90507FF8DFE08F8EA9E65442F" box="[391,572,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="47">E. oxyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having coxa IV with one transversal, proapical, acute and conical apophysis but can be distinguished by the following characters: short (shorter than trochanter IV width) probasal apophysis on trochanter IV, high ocularium with spine, and femur IV with proventral and retroventral rows of acuminate tubercles increasing in size apically.
</paragraph>
