</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FDA1980B4179" blockId="14.[189,1106,496,558]" box="[189,1106,531,558]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">MEASUREMENTS. DSL 3.77, DSW 3.19, femur I 2.38, II 4.80, III 3.25, IV 4.49.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FDE39D714075" blockId="14.[189,1399,598,802]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
DORSUM (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E0502FF88FEBEFDE39DEB4127" box="[305,434,598,624]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,431,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-47@12.[189,1398,425,1848]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628985/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 7A, C</figureCitation>
). Blunt PAM; acuminate median paracheliceral projection similar in size to PAM. High ocularium with median spine (about twice times ocularium height). Carapace with scattered granules. Scutal areas I–IV with scattered granules with some tubercles among them. Posterior margin of dorsal scutum with scattered granules. Lateral margins with blunt tubercles about the same size as those on the scUtUm. Free tergites I–III with a defined row of granUles. Anal opercUlUm with scattered granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FCFE9D6840DF" blockId="14.[188,1399,842,904]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
VENTER (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E0502FF88FEA4FCFF9DDF4032" box="[299,390,842,869]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,431,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-47@12.[189,1398,425,1848]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 7. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628985/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
). Coxa I with irregular row of setiferous tubercles, coxae II–IV densely and irregularly granulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FC0598C2409D" blockId="14.[189,1179,944,970]" box="[189,1179,944,970]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">CHELICERAE. Segment I with two ectal-basal tubercles and one mesal-basal tubercle.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FC479FAF4778" blockId="14.[189,1399,1010,1072]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">PEDIPALPS. Trochanter with sparse tubercles dorsally. Femur with one mesal apical setiferous tubercle. Tibia setation: ectal IiIi, mesal IiIi; tarsus setation: ectal IIIi, mesal IIi.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32FBED992E478A" blockId="14.[189,1400,1111,1245]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
LEGS (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E0502FF88FE84FBE29D0B4725" box="[267,338,1111,1138]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[254,1324,265,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-15@13.[254,1334,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 8. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386). A–B. Femur IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. C–D. Femur III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. E–F. Patella and tibia IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. G–H. Patella and tibia III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. I– J. Detail of trochanter IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. Scale bars: A–H = 0.5 mm; I–J = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628987" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628987/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Coxae I–III with scattered granules; coxa IV with one transversal, prolateral and apical apophysis, which is conical and short. Trochanters I–IV with scattered tubercles; trochanter IV with one probasal apophysis, which is conical, short and dorsally oriented. Femur III with proventral and retroventral rows of acute tubercles increasing in size apically; tibia III with proventral and retroventral
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5D66730502FF88FF32F81E9F3444BE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628989" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4628989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628989/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="50" startId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" targetBox="[189,1398,1293,1925]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0502FF88FF32F81E9F3444BE" blockId="14.[189,1399,1963,2025]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B956EAE90502FF88FF32F81E9D574492" bold="true" box="[189,270,1963,1989]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Fig. 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C224D780502FF88FE96F8199DAD4492" authority="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira, 2021" authorityName="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2021" box="[281,500,1963,1989]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="14" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xambioa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B956EAE90502FF88FE96F8199DAD4492" box="[281,500,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">Eusarcus xambioa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26557920502FF88FE70F8199E394491" box="[511,608,1964,1990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), distal part of penis. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE90502FF88FB37F81E98944492" bold="true" box="[1208,1229,1963,1989]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">A</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE90502FF88FF32F87B9C8844BF" bold="true" box="[189,209,1998,2024]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">B</emphasis>
. Ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B956EAE90502FF88FE0FF87B9DCC44BF" bold="true" box="[384,405,1998,2024]" pageId="14" pageNumber="50">C</emphasis>
. Right lateral view. Scale bars = 50 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0503FF89FF32FEBC98F4423E" blockId="15.[188,1400,265,362]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">rows of acuminate tubercles. Femur IV slightly sinuous, with small PDS and RDS, proventral row of acuminate tubercles increasing in size apically and retroventral row with reduced tubercles; tibia IV with proventral and retroventral rows of acuminate tubercles increasing in size subapically.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0503FF89FF32FE2498814143" blockId="15.[189,1399,401,533]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">
PENIS (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E0503FF89FE9DFE249D0442FC" box="[274,349,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1293,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-252@14.[189,1398,1293,1925]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), distal part of penis. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Right lateral view. Scale bars = 50 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4628989/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Ventral plate with substraight lateral margins; distal margin slightly concave; ventral surface entirely covered with 
<typeStatus id="549988590503FF89FDAAFE009E014298" box="[549,600,437,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
T1 microsetae; with three pairs of lateral-distal MS C1–C3, three pairs of A1, one pair of B1, one pair of minute D1 and E1 absent. Stylus with ventrally-tilted medianventral trichomes. Ventral process tUbUlar, cUrved, with apex with flabelliform projection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36FB0503FF89FF32FD899E8A412D" blockId="15.[189,1398,572,634]" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">
COLOURATION (in alcohol) (
<figureCitation id="13192A7E0503FF89FD89FD899E2A4101" box="[518,627,572,598]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStartId-0="12.[189,232,1887,1913]" captionStartId-1="13.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox-0="[189,1398,431,1848]" captionTargetBox-1="[254,1324,265,1854]" captionTargetId-0="figure-47@12.[189,1398,425,1848]" captionTargetId-1="figure-15@13.[254,1334,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId-0="12" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="Fig. 7. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386), habitUs. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C. Lateral view. Scale bars: A–B = 1 mm; C = 0.5 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 8. Eusarcus xambioa sp. nov., ♂, holotype (ISLA 60386). A–B. Femur IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. C–D. Femur III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. E–F. Patella and tibia IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. G–H. Patella and tibia III, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. I– J. Detail of trochanter IV, dorsal and ventral view, respectively. Scale bars: A–H = 0.5 mm; I–J = 0.2 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628985" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4628987" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4628985/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4628987/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="51">Figs 7–8</figureCitation>
). Body and appendages background colour Deep Orange Yellow (69), appendages Strong Orange Yellow (68).
</paragraph>
